    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>NEW ROLE FOR FORMER CANADIAN LEADER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brian Mulroney, former prime minister of Canada, chairman of the Sun Media Corp, has temporarily become its chief executive after the surprise resignation of Paul Godfrey; Mulroney photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Brian Mulroney, 61, left, who was prime minister of Canada from 1984 to 1993 and is the chairman of the Sun Media Corporation, has temporarily become its chief executive after the surprise resignation of Paul Godfrey. Mr. Mulroney was president of the Iron Ore Company of Canada before he was elected leader of the Progressive Conservative Party in 1983.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard (NYT)</p>
      </block>
